related_questions.question: What is the difference between a travel adapter and converter?
related_questions.snippet: A travel adapter (sometimes called a travel plug converter) enables you to plug your electronics into walls with different sockets than the one used by your country. ... The US uses a plug with two flat vertical prongs whereas the UK uses a plug with one top vertical prong and two bottom horizontal prongs.

related_questions.question: Can I plug a power strip into a travel adapter?
related_questions.snippet: Fortunately, you don't have to. Instead, buy a travel power strip (or in a pinch, just pack one you've got lying around at home).
